-pcgP7u55QQ.description:

The Trustees & the Managing Council of Sri Sathya Trust Maharashtra are pleased to invite you for the 
For the 54th Annual day celebrations of  “ Dharmakshetra “ on 12th May 2021.

7.00 pm  Omkar  followed by introduction to the speakers for the evening by Brother Shivkumar Kanan
7.05 pm “Dharmakshetra’  the origin and the establishment of the Epitome of Divinity by Sister Rani Java
7.25 pm  “Installation & Consecration of Love in the divine Figurine” by Brother Vijay Santhanam
7.35pm  “Dharmakshetra your soul mate for a divine life” by Brother Siddharth Bhat.
7.50 pm Concluding remarks by All India President – Shri . Nimish Pandya
7.55 pm Vote of Thanks by MMR State President – Shri. Anoop Saxena
8.00 pm  Aarti from Dharmakshetra.

uqiIAYcInxk.title: "Easwaramma" - Poornavatar Ke Janani
uqiIAYcInxk.description:
Sairam
A humble offering by Mahila youth of MMR to Divine mother Easwaramma.

Lyrics & Tune: - S SRINIVASAN -NERUL
MUSIC & VIDEO ARRANGEMENTS: - VINU MOHAN (SK DIGITAL GRAPHICS STUDIO- MUMBAI)
LEAD SINGERS: - MRS. LAXMI VINU/ASWINI SRIDHAR/VAISHNAVI/KRITI BALAJI
FLUTE: - SHRI. PRAMOD

Lyrics: 
Poornavatar ke janani tum ho 
Dhanya ho tum easwaramma.

Shanti prem ka beej boya 
Manav seva ka jyot jalaya 
 Prakat huwe jab sai tujhse 
Baje  saaj aur vadya mrudanga

Poonavatar ke janani tum.ho
Dhanya ho tum easwaramma  

Saadgi ka prateek tum ho
Tyag ka pratiswaroop tum ho
Karuna moorthi divya janani
Prema sagara easwaramna

Poonavatar ke janani tum.ho
Dhanya ho tum. easwaramma 

Shafakhana, jal pariyojan 
 Shiksha sanstha karke nirman
Manav ka uddhar kiya sai
Sai sankalp ka Adhaar tum ho
Divya janani daya sagari


Poonavatar ke janani tum.ho
Dhanya ho tum. easwaramma


Meaning: 
You are the divine mother of complete divine incarnation of God 
Hail oh mother easwaramma 

You sowed the seed of love n peace into Sai
You lit the lamp of service to mankind in Sai's heart
When sai was born from your womb, mother
All musical instruments started playing on its own.

You are the divine mother of complete divine incarnation of God 
Hail oh mother easwaramma 

You are the symbol of simplicity
You are the epitome of sacrifice
You are the ocean of compassion, eternal mother
You are the ocean of love mother easwaramma. 

You are the divine mother of complete divine incarnation of God 
Hail oh mother easwaramma 

You are the reason etre or foundation for swami's resolution
 Super speciality hospitals and water projects
By establishing Educational institutions, 
You redeemed the mankind with these kind deeds sai
Eternal mother you are the ocean of compassion.

You are the divine mother of complete divine incarnation of God 
Hail oh mother easwaramma

Zbs6vm2_RTs.title: Aradhana Mahotsavam Special | Sri Sathya Sai Youth | Mumbai
Zbs6vm2_RTs.description:
#AradhanaMahotsavamSong #MMRYouth #OSai O Sai | Original Song |

'O Sai' is a humble offering of the MMR Youth at the Divine Lotus Feet of our beloved Bhagwan on the auspicious occasion of Aradhana Day.

Singers: Sashi Kiran Kurucheti, Srishanth Shetty, Sai Pragnan Bhyravabhatla

Flute: Pramod Umapathi

Tabla: Sai Santosha Pidatala

Additional Percussion: Sai Hruday Pidatala 

Keyboards & Music Programming: Sai Pragnan Bhyravabhatla

Mix & Mastering: Sai Teja Bhagavatula

Lyrics & Composition: Samya Bhattacharya

Lyrics:

Aaye fir tere dwar pe hai hum - O Sai 
Tere Bina Raha Na Jaaye Ek Pal - O Sai 

Zindegi Ki Har Ek Subhah
Tum Se Huyi Roshan
Gham Mein Bhi Jo Hum Huye Bezubaan 
Tum Ne Diye Darshan

Tere Sahare to hum Jiliye 
Tere Sharan mein hai Rehna 

Tum jo mile toh sab paa liye
Jo Tum na mile Sab khoya

Tere Bina Raha Na Jaaye Ek Pal - O Sai 
Aaye fir tere dwar pe hai hum - O Sai



~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PjLWOwLxwVU.description:
#BhajanUtsav #SriSathyaSaiYouth #Mumbai

Aum Sri Sai Ram 

Mumbai Metro Region Sai Youth Presents a Special Episode of the Bhajan Utsav in the special birthday month of November. Namasmarana Special episode covers the essence of singing Bhajans. useful tips for adding Bhava in our bhajans and most importantly explaining the different types of Sankirthanas - All these taken from different Bhajan workshops conducted by brothers Shri Ravi Kumar, Shri Amey Deshpande & Shri Siddhartha Raju from the Prashanti Bhajan Group.

JYlEX-40x7A.title: 95th Birthday Song | Tum Ho Sab Ke Bhagwan | Sri Sathya Sai Youth | Mumbai
JYlEX-40x7A.description:
#95thBirthdaySong #MMRYouth #TumHoSabKeBhagwan

'Tum Ho Sab Ke Bhagwan' is a humble offering of the MMR Youth at the Divine Lotus Feet of our beloved Bhagwan on the auspicious occasion of Swami's 95th Birthday. 

Lyrics: 

Sairam... Sairam... (2)

Tum ho sab ke Bhagwan
Jag mein sab se pyara naam 

Tum ho Rama.
Tum ho Krishna.
Tum Kaliyug Avtara.

Sairam... Sairam... (2)


Tumhare sharan mein daas rakho sai
Man mandir ho Dwarkamai

Kripa karo prabhu antaryami
Parthi puri dil mein ho Swami

Har dil ho ek mandir, Sai
Har roz ho tumhara janam

Har Dhadkan Tum ko Arpan (Sai)
Har Chintan mein Dijo Darshan

Sairam... Sairam...



Meaning: 

O Supreme Master Sai, You are the beloved lord of all. The Sweetness of your name enchants the world 
You are the incarnation of Lord Rama. You are the incarnation of Lord Krishna. You are the incarnation of this Kali Age. 
I implore you to let me be a servitor of your lotus feet. O divine mother you reside in our hearts. O indweller of our hearts, Omniscient bestow on us your mercy and compassion. O Lord who dwells in Parthi, you also reside in our hearts. May all our hearts transform into a place worthy for your residence. May every day be a celebration of your birth. We prayerfully offer our heart and soul to you O Lord Sai.
We pray to you to grant us your darshan in all thoughts.


Like | Share | Subscribe

q4jlKlGDzaM.title: The Path Divine - An introduction to the Sri Sathya Sai Balvikas
q4jlKlGDzaM.description:
This film is an introduction to the Balvikas movement started by Sri Sathya Sai Baba in 1969. Watch the film to know more about this Divine project. 

Half a century ago, a silent mission began, which would slowly start transforming the shape of the youth of this world in the years to come. Sri Sathya Sai Baba started the Bal Vikas movement, where men and women, with abundant love for Bhagavaan, started teaching the five Human values to children in their neighbourhoods. These were Satya (Truth), Dharma (Righteousness), Shanti (Peace), Prem (Love) and Ahimsa (Non-violence).

Sathya Sai Baba believed that there is only one religion, the religion of love and humanity. If one wants to love God, one must serve his fellowmen, and through the process realise that the divinity he's looking for in Temples, Mosques or Churches, is in fact within him. He thus wanted to inculcate these 5 human values to children from a tender age of 6, so they get into a habit of listening to their conscience and get used to the voice of God within them when difficult situations and decisions arise in life. 

The Balvikas Programme today is spread all over the world, and lakhs of children have benefitted from this Divine blessing in these 50 years of this movement. In this 9 year course, from age 6 to age 15, a child gradually blossoms into an individual who is well equipped to face the world as a young adult infused with self confidence and the assurance that the voice of conscience within him is his guiding light.

JEszRGTUR2I.title: (Part 4)Rituraj Ji Maharaj Shrimad Bhagwatam Prashanthi Nilayam
JEszRGTUR2I.description:
The Bhagavatam says that the stories and deeds of God are beyond comprehension. Non one can understand His sports, but listening to them generates bliss in the heart and grants immortality. Such is the nature of divinity. 

Consider radio waves transmitted from Delhi, Bangalore, Madras, Calcutta, Sri Lanka even America, No two waves mingle. What a mystery, there is no confusion between the millions of waves in the air, when does the confusion arise? Only when we do not tune into the correct station. This “tuning” is meditation. Tune your mind with concentration to receive the “news”, namely, divine vision. When the mind is divergent, the reception is unclean or meaningless.
JEszRGTUR2I.channelTitle: Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations Maharashtra Goa

localized.title: Rituraj Ji Maharaj Shrimad Bhagwatam Prasanthi Nilayam Part   1   YouTube 360p
localized.description:
The Bhagavatam says that the stories and deeds of God are beyond comprehension. Non one can understand His sports, but listening to them generates bliss in the heart and grants immortality. Such is the nature of divinity. 

Consider radio waves transmitted from Delhi, Bangalore, Madras, Calcutta, Sri Lanka even America, No two waves mingle. What a mystery, there is no confusion between the millions of waves in the air, when does the confusion arise? Only when we do not tune into the correct station. This “tuning” is meditation. Tune your mind with concentration to receive the “news”, namely, divine vision. When the mind is divergent, the reception is unclean or meaningless.

Et6x0Q0XuUI.title: Mother Easwaramma Foundation, Mumbai
Et6x0Q0XuUI.description:
Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba has always bestowed the highest honour on 'Women'. 
Baba continuously guides us to revere the Mother as God. He has himself, in this, Avatar, fulfilled His mother's desires. The Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning, the Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Medical Sciences and the Sri Sathya Sai Water Project are testimony to the three promises he made to his mother. 

This short documentary is an insight into one is the several such programs he initiated for the welfare of women which has now been effectively running for 3 decades and has benefited more than 5000 students thus far. This short-film was produced in April 2012 by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation & Kotloos Studio at Dharmakshetra, Mumbai.
Et6x0Q0XuUI.channelTitle: Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations Maharashtra Goa

This short-film was produced in April 2012 by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation & Kotloos Studio at Dharmakshetra, Mumbai.

HzHmFVJ8vQs.description:
If they cannot come to you, You go to their doorsteps. This was Bhagwan Baba's love and guideline. Since people in remote villages do not have access to timely medication, we must go and provide this basic need. Its been 10 years now. 36 mobile medical vans go on a fixed schedule to the remotest parts of Maharashtra and provide basic to intermediary level medical services to the needy becoming the only organisation to take up a project of this scale on a consistent basis. 

This short documentary was produced in April 2012 by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation and Kotloos Studio in Maharashtra.

4Ufl1P3W2Wg.description:
Education begins at home. With changing times, families and schools are unable to spend the kind of energy and time to impart values in a form that the child can absorb readily. Bhagawan Baba took this challenge head on and started the Bal vikas program a few decades ago. Over years, this program has been replicated this way in every state of the country and many other countries. watch what it is all about!

This short documentary was produced in April 2012 by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation and Kotloos Studio in Maharashtra.
